<subSubSection id="CFBD651F910D595CACAEDF1B2012FA15" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph id="87183694910D595CACAEDF1B206BFB75" blockId="6.[868,1495,602,1362]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
This species was described based on a single specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="FFB07604910D595CACC8DF3B217AFD35" box="[1005,1085,634,659]" name="Mexico" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(no further details). Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="E3364B65910D595CAAA1DF3B26ECFD15" author="Buquet, J. B. L." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refId="ref14776" refString="Buquet, J. B. L. 1844. In: Guerin-Meneville, F. E. Iconographie du regne animal de G. Cuvier, ou representation d'apres nature de l'une des especes les plus remarquables et souvent non enconre figurees, de chaque genre d'animaux (Insectes). Paris, J. B. Bailliere. v. 7, 576 p." type="book" year="1844">Buquet (1844)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<emphasis id="B5D3EA86910D595CAB0EDFDB2052FD15" box="[1067,1301,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="40A74D17910D595CAB0EDFDB2055FD15" box="[1067,1298,666,691]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Eriphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unipunctatus">Eriphus unipunctatus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but the 
<typeStatus id="581C8836910D595CAA59DFDB20E9FD15" box="[1404,1454,666,691]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
locality is unknown (“Hab. inconnue”). 
<bibRefCitation id="E3364B65910D595CAA3DDFFB2092FD75" author="Chevrolat, L. A." box="[1304,1493,698,723]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="747 - 763" refId="ref14843" refString="Chevrolat, L. A. 1862. Revision des genres Eriphus et Mallosoma Serville, du groupe des clytides et description de trois nouveaux genres dont un doit etre rapporte au groupe des callidiites. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, Quatrieme Serie, 2: 747 - 763." type="journal article" year="1862">Chevrolat (1862)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="40A74D17910D595CAB2CDF9B21F0FD55" box="[1033,1207,730,755]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Eriphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unipunctatus">
<emphasis id="B5D3EA86910D595CAB2CDF9B21F0FD55" box="[1033,1207,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">E. unipunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="40A74D17910D595CAA2DDF9B20DDFD55" authorityName="Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1834" box="[1288,1434,730,755]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Eriphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="B5D3EA86910D595CAA2DDF9B20DDFD55" box="[1288,1434,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">E. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and indicated 
<collectingCountry id="FFB07604910D595CACF3DFBB2161FCB5" box="[982,1062,762,787]" name="Mexico" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Mexico</collectingCountry>
as the country where the species occurs. According to him (translated): “Collection of Mr. J. Thomson. The 
<typeStatus id="581C8836910D595CAB2ADE7B2106FCF5" box="[1039,1089,826,851]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
of Serville no longer existed when I acquired almost all of the 
<taxonomicName id="40A74D17910D595CABB8DE1B207BFCD5" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[1181,1340,858,883]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cerambycidae</taxonomicName>
from this author”. 
<bibRefCitation id="E3364B65910D595CAC88DE3B211BFC35" author="Monne, M. A." box="[941,1116,890,915]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refId="ref16230" refString="Monne, M. A. 1994 a. Catalogue of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of the Western Hemisphere. Part XI. Subfamily Cerambycinae: Tribes Torneutini, Trachyderini and Basipterini. Sao Paulo, Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia. 157 p." type="book" year="1994">Monné (1994a)</bibRefCitation>
indicated 
<taxonomicName id="40A74D17910D595CABFBDE3B2029FC35" authorityName="Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1834" box="[1246,1390,890,915]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Eriphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="B5D3EA86910D595CABFBDE3B2029FC35" box="[1246,1390,890,915]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">E. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as from 
<collectingCountry id="FFB07604910D595CAC40DEDB26E6FC15" box="[869,929,922,947]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="4563F876910D595CAC97DEDB2115FC15" box="[946,1106,922,947]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="4563F876910D595CABB7DEDB207AFC15" box="[1170,1341,922,947]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
), and 
<bibRefCitation id="E3364B65910D595CAAA3DEDB2161FC75" author="Monne, M. A. &amp; Fragoso, S. A." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="113 - 120" refId="ref16473" refString="Monne, M. A. &amp; Fragoso, S. A. 1996. Sobre Eriphus Audinet-Serville, 1834 e Athetesis Bates, 1870 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Cerambycinae, Trachyderini). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 40 (1): 113 - 120." type="journal article" year="1996">Monné &amp; Fragoso (1996)</bibRefCitation>
confirmed this information. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="E3364B65910D595CAC40DE9B213BFC55" author="Monne, M. A. &amp; Giesbert, E. F." box="[869,1148,986,1011]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refId="ref16559" refString="Monne, M. A. &amp; Giesbert, E. F. 1994. Checklist of the Cerambycidae and Disteniidae (Coleoptera) of the Western Hemisphere. Burbank, Wolfsgarden Books. 409 p." type="book" year="1994">Monné &amp; Giesbert (1994)</bibRefCitation>
listed the species from 
<collectingCountry id="FFB07604910D595CAAA0DE9B2092FC55" box="[1413,1493,986,1011]" name="Mexico" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="FFB07604910D595CACBEDEBB26B0FBB5" box="[923,1015,1018,1043]" name="Panama" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Panama</collectingCountry>
. Usually, the inclusions of new records in this checklist were based on Giesbert’s private collection, which is currently deposited at FSCA. It will be necessary to examine the specimens to confirm if they are 
<emphasis id="B5D3EA86910D595CAAA6D91B26EDFB35" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="40A74D17910D595CAAA6D91B26E1FB35" authorityName="Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1834" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Eriphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">E. mexicanus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
If they are 
<emphasis id="B5D3EA86910D595CAB0CD93B21FEFB35" box="[1065,1209,1146,1171]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="40A74D17910D595CAB0CD93B21F2FB35" authorityName="Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1834" box="[1065,1205,1146,1171]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Eriphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">E. mexicanus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
this indicate that 
<taxonomicName id="40A74D17910D595CAAA6D93B26E3FB15" authorityName="Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1834" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Eriphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="B5D3EA86910D595CAAA6D93B26E3FB15" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">E. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="40A74D17910D595CACF8D9DB21C3FB15" box="[989,1156,1178,1203]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Eriphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unipunctatus">
<emphasis id="B5D3EA86910D595CACF8D9DB21C3FB15" box="[989,1156,1178,1203]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">E. unipunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not the same species, due to the isolated geographical distribution.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87183694910D595CACAED99B2092FA95" blockId="6.[868,1495,602,1362]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
The specimen examined by us agrees perfectly with the original descriptions and with the photograph of the 
<typeStatus id="581C8836910D595CAC40D85B268DFA95" box="[869,970,1306,1331]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis id="B5D3EA86910D595CACCDD85B21D5FA95" box="[1000,1170,1306,1331]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="40A74D17910D595CACCDD85B21C9FA95" box="[1000,1166,1306,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Eriphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unipunctatus">E.unipunctatus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
differing only by the absence
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87183694910D595CAC41D87B2092FA35" blockId="6.[868,1495,602,1362]" lastBlockId="6.[869,1493,1402,1459]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
of the black spot on base of the pronotum. 
<emphasis id="B5D3EA86910D595CAC40D83B210CFA35" bold="true" box="[869,1099,1402,1427]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Material examined:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="FFB07604910D595CAB77D83B21E5FA35" box="[1106,1186,1402,1427]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">BRASIL</collectingCountry>
, 
<emphasis id="B5D3EA86910D595CAB89D83B2001FA35" box="[1196,1350,1402,1427]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<collectingRegion id="4563F876910D595CAB89D83B2007FA35" box="[1196,1344,1402,1427]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
:
</emphasis>
Aracruz, 
<specimenCount id="91A1FD1D910D595CAA89D83B2097FA34" box="[1452,1488,1399,1427]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="female">1 ♀</specimenCount>
,
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87183694910D595CAC40D8DB2012FA15" blockId="6.[869,1493,1402,1459]" box="[869,1365,1434,1459]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<date id="F3191054910D595CAC40D8DB2693FA15" box="[869,980,1434,1459]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1986-10-12">12.X.1986</date>
, J.B. Silva col. (MZSP, formerly SSA).
</paragraph>
